  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: e9620f8c34305754d8cc9a7e49e852d9, type: 3}
  m_Name: Enemies_en
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Unity.Localization::UnityEngine.Localization.Tables.StringTable
  m_LocaleId:
    m_Code: en
  m_SharedData: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 3f63dd2e5b3a9b64d93105ba50b014b3, type: 2}
  m_Metadata:
    m_Items: []
  m_TableData:
  - m_Id: 73614639104
    m_Localized: When the cataclysm happened, the animals known as cats were transformed
      into these viscous, semi-liquid creatures. Curious by nature, they still maintain
      the habit of rubbing as a sign of affection. However, due to their new acidic
      physiology, contact with them causes serious harm, so it's best to avoid them.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 83978764288
    m_Localized: It seems that the viscous substance that makes up their new body
      does not withstand heat well.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 6346391552
    m_Localized: Slimecat
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1205179138048
    m_Localized: Fleech
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1207590862848
    m_Localized: These flying creatures are abundant in the area, sucking nutrients
      from any living being they encounter. They attack by swooping down on their
      target, so you need good reflexes to dodge them.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1209830621184
    m_Localized: Despite spending their time sucking energy from others, they are
      greatly hurt when they receive a taste of their own medicine.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1255779221504
    m_Localized: Lupin Bandit (Claws)
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1257989619712
    m_Localized: When the catastrophe struck, those who were most aggressive took
      on this appearance. Now they all live together in a pack and spend their days
      fighting and attacking any unsuspecting traveler. Some attack by tearing off
      their arms and growing claws to deliver powerful slashes.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1260002885632
    m_Localized: Their lycanthrope abilities make them more resilient under the moonlight.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1317678759936
    m_Localized: Lupin Bandit (Shooter)
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1319754940416
    m_Localized: When the catastrophe struck, those who were most aggressive took
      on this appearance. Now they all live together in a pack and spend their days
      fighting and attacking any unsuspecting traveler. Some attack by splitting
      their heads in two and shooting fangs from inside.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1321327804416
    m_Localized: At night, their shots are more deadly.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1385718759424
    m_Localized: Wolfkira
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1387228708864
    m_Localized: In the society of the lupin bandits, the law of the strongest prevails,
      and Wolfkira masters this law perfectly. Her great strength combined with her
      cunning has allowed her to maintain her undefeated title as alpha of the pack,
      crushing anyone who dares to challenge her. She rejoices in fighting and accumulating
      the belongings that she and her gang steal from their victims. There is no
      greater pleasure for her than finding a worthy rival capable of forcing her
      to use her skills to the fullest.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1388658966528
    m_Localized: 
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1437086400512
    m_Localized: Lumbearjack
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1438520852480
    m_Localized: Having lived since before the world went mad, Lumbearjack has endured
      much and harbors a deep-seated grudge against the roots of the great tree,
      which he blames for everything that has happened. Wielding his axe-like arm,
      he aims to destroy all the roots and dreams of the day he can fell the great
      tree. Perhaps living so long has taken its toll on his mind, hence this deep
      and irrational hatred.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1439896584192
    m_Localized: 
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  references:
    version: 2
    RefIds: []
